<br>
It's been a LONG time since I've posted one of these.<br>
<br>
One thing I want to really point out to everyone. This isn't the new Flamevault or anything of the sort. This is the Safehouse. A place for mature discussions, debates, and to share comeradity(sp?) - with a focus on Rogues. I am not expecting happy happy joy love (TM) in every post. Just that you respect this community, and adhere to the forum rules - despite the flak we get about overmoderating they aren't that strict.<br>
<br>
If you have an issue you want to bring to our attention, email any of the mods or myself.  Our emails are very public.<br>
<br>
Ok, now that I've gotten the ugliness out of the way...<br>
<br>
<B>Upcoming Changes</B><br>
<br>
The forums are going to be restructured in the upcoming days.  <br>
-Categories will be added to better organize the forums<br>
-The Recruitment and Fence's Booth forums will be removed, abolished, history... <br>
-DAoC Forum will be added<br>
-Alot of the Library items (if not all) will be moved to the Resources section of our website.<br>
<br>
<B>Seeking a volunteer</B><br>
Along that topic, I am looking for someone to volunteer to help with extracting all the excellent info from the Back Alley, Quest and Laboratory forums.  This person must be willing to scour these forums on a daily or semi-daily basis and compile them into readable guides.  Shoot me an email at zato@thesafehouse.org if you are interested and tell me a bit about yourself.<br>
<br>
<B>T-Shirts</B><br>
Tshirts were lowered again in price.  We are not selling these to line our pockets folks, basically just trying to recoup the initial investment.  We could have had another company provide these - but the quality would have most likely been worse and the price definately would have been much higher.<br>
<br>
<B>A hearty THANKS</B><br>
Now please bear with me a second, I want to give credit to those that deserve it and I don't do this often enough.<br>
<br>
Thanks to the great moderators for their fine work (in no particular order), Shadowcross, Fiae, Tibis, Fricka, Garrik, and Glip (with honorable mention for his dedication to upholding the Ring).  Thanks to Kezzek for keeping this place going when I faltered, to Vaslin for his outstanding insight, and to Aidden for all his help.  Thanks to Remmi for returning to us and being... well,  Remmi :).<br>
<br>
Finally thanks to all the great people who come here and contribute every day.  This is an amazing community and it's all because of you.<br>
<br>
EDIT:  Now that Kezzek made it official - he is steppig back from the Safehouse so he can focus on other things.  Kez, you will be dearly missed my friend.<br>
<br>
